<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: characteristic_type
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.characteristic_type">
A <b>characteristic_type</b> is a group that specifies a boolean property, a numeric property whose units are in accordance with ISO 10303-41, a compound characteristic, a
logical property, a string property, or an externally defined property for a characteristic.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: characteristic_type.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.characteristic_type.wr:WR1">
A <b>characteristic_type</b> shall have a name that is 
'string property', 
'logical property', 
'boolean property',
'numeric property',
'externally defined property' or
'compound characteristic'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: coordinated_representation_item
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.coordinated_representation_item">
<note> The local rules for this entity have not been fully updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

A <b>coordinated_representation_item</b> is a representation and a  <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/>
that implements the ARM concepts of:
</p><ul>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Characteristic:arm:Characteristic_arm.Plus_minus_tolerance_characteristic"/></li>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Characteristic:arm:Characteristic_arm.Statistical_tolerance_characteristic"/></li>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Characteristic:arm:Characteristic_arm.Symmetrical_tolerance_characteristic"/></li>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Characteristic:arm:Characteristic_arm.Tolerance_characteristic"/></li>
</ul>
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: coordinated_representation_item.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.coordinated_representation_item.wr:WR1">
The <b>coordinated_representation_item</b> shall represent at most one property
that is an element of at most one  <express_ref linkend="material_property_representation_schema:ir_express:material_property_representation_schema.data_environment"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: coordinated_representation_item.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.coordinated_representation_item.wr:WR2">
The <b>coordinated_representation_item</b> shall be referenced by exactly one
document.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: coordinated_representation_item.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.coordinated_representation_item.wr:WR3">
If the <b>coordinated_representation_item</b> has a  <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> name of
'tolerance', it shall contain at least one  <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.measure_representation_item"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: coordinated_representation_item.WR4
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.coordinated_representation_item.wr:WR4">
<!-- Done, MTK 3/19/97 -->
If the <b>coordinated_representation_item</b> has a  <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> name of
'plus minus tolerance', it shall contain exactly three 
measure_representation_items.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: coordinated_representation_item.WR5
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.coordinated_representation_item.wr:WR5">
If the <b>coordinated_representation_item</b> has a  <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> name of
'symmetrical tolerance', it shall contain exactly two 
measure_representation_items.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: coordinated_representation_item.WR6
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.coordinated_representation_item.wr:WR6">
<!-- Done, MTK 3/23/97 -->
If the <b>coordinated_representation_item</b> has a  <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> name
of 'plus minus tolerance', the three contained measure_representation_items
shall have their name attribute satisfied by 'basic value', 'plus value',
and 'minus value'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: coordinated_representation_item.WR7
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.coordinated_representation_item.wr:WR7">
<!-- Done, MTK 3/23/97 -->
If the <b>coordinated_representation_item</b> has a  <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/> name of
'symmetrical tolerance', the two contained measure_representation_items
shall have their name attribute satisfied by 'basic value' and
'deviation value'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: parameter_type
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.parameter_type">
<note> The local rules for this entity have not been fully updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

A <b>parameter_type</b> is a group that specifies a boolean_property_type, a
logical_property_type, a physical_property_type or a string_property_type
for a  <express_ref linkend="Model_parameter:mim:Model_parameter_mim.model_parameter"/>.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: parameter_type.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Characteristic_mim.parameter_type.wr:WR1">
A <b>parameter_type</b> shall have a name that is 'string property type', 'logical
property type', 'physical property type', or 'boolean property type'.
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>
